 two sides in any newspaper. \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Devonport\n| score = 47\u201321\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Senior Club Matches/Devonport and Marist Win\n| page = 4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18820\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240922.2.7.5\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Athletic\n| try1 = [[Allan Seagar]] 3, Harry Douglas, [[Bert Laing]], L Voysey 3, G Smith, [[Stan Webb (rugby league)|Stan Webb]], A Harper\n| con1 = [[Bert Laing]] 2, Scott 3, [[Stan Webb (rugby league)|Stan Webb]], J Laing\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 2, Weeks, Timmins, McGregor\n| con2 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 2\n| pen2 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Marist\n| score = 34\u201317\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Senior Club Matches/Devonport and Marist Win\n| page = 4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18820\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240922.2.7.5\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Richmond\n| try1 = Johnson 2, W Kirkland, J Stormont, George Gardiner, Mallory, Sweeney, Carroll\n| con1 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]] 5\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = K Hyland 2, W Hanlon\n| con2 = W Hanlon 3\n| pen2 = W Hanlon\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = W Mincham\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 2:00\n| home = Ellerslie\n| score = 6\u20133\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Senior Club Matches/Ellerslie Defeat Newton\n| page = 4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18820\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240922.2.7.5\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = O\u2019Brien, Shane\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Thompson\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Ellerslie Reserve\n| attendance =\n| referee = Hill\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Mangere\n| score = ?-?\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Senior Club Matches/Devonport and Marist Win/Ellerslie Defeat Newton\n| page = 4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18820\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240922.2.7.5\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Manukau\n| attendance =\n| referee = Coulam\n}}\n\n======Final======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Marist\n| score = 20\u201317\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Marist Win Final Replay/Twenty Points to Seventeen/Devonport Just Beaten\n| page =6\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18826\n| date = 1924-09-29\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240929.2.12.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Devonport\n| try1 = J Stormont, [[Jack Kirwan]], Billy Ghent, Malloy\n| con1 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]] 3\n| pen1 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]]\n| try2 = [[Bert Laing]], A Harper, Harry Douglas\n| con2 = [[Bert Laing]], Scott\n| pen2 = [[Bert Laing]] 2\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 17000\n| referee =\n}}\n\nTwo matches were postponed in Round 4 as the league decided that they wanted the #1 field in the best possible condition for the exhibition match between [[City Rovers]] and Marist Old Boys of [[Christchurch]]. The weather had been particularly poor in the lead up with the previous weekend seeing all football in [[Auckland]] cancelled. These postponed matches were unique in that they were eventually played 10 days later on a Tuesday morning at 9.30am. This would surely be one of the only times a senior match had been played on a working weekday morning in the competitions history.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Postponed Club Matches/Played This Morning/Marists and Athletics Draw/Ellerslie Brings Off a Surprise\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=55| issue=130\n| date = 1923-06-03\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240603.2.109\n| accessdate = 2019-09-05}}</ref>\n\nThere was controversy in the Round 7 match between [[City Rovers]] and [[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond]] as the City team fielded [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] who had not been granted clearance by either [[Auckland Rugby League]] or [[New Zealand Rugby League]]. [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Brown]] had previously played for [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] and had been released to play for [[Wigan Warriors|Wigan]] in [[England]]. After returning he wanted to turn out for the [[City Rovers|City]] club but [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] claimed that he had been released on the grounds that he would return to play for them alone. Brown was later suspended for 3 matches before rejoining the [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] team for their match against [[Marist Saints|Marist]].<ref>{{cite news\n| authors = John Coffey & Bernie Wood\n| title =Auckland 100 Years of Rugby League 1909\u20132009\n| pages =77\u201378\n| publisher =Huia Publishers\n| date = 2009}}</ref>\n\n[[City Rovers]] defaulted their Round 9 match with [[Mangere Rugby League Football Club|Mangere]] after their dispute with the [[Auckland Rugby League]] when they refused to take the field.\n\n== Roope Rooster Knockout Competition ==\n[[City Rovers]] won the Roope Rooster for the 4th time in their history, defeating [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] who were attempting to win their third consecutive title, in the final by 6 points to 5.\n\n======Round 1======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Richmond\n| score = 11\u20137\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ellerslie Beat Richmond\n| page =6\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18826\n| date = 1924-09-29\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240929.2.12.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Ellerslie\n| try1 = Hunt, Echrafft, R Hyland\n| con1 = W Hanlon\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Clarke\n| con2 = Shand\n| pen2 =\n| drop2=Shand\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n\n======Round 2======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Devonport\n| score = 5\u20133\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title = Knock-Out Competition/Devonport Beat Marist\n| page =5\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18832\n| date = 1924-10-06\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19241006.2.31.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Marist\n| try1 = A Harper\n| con1 =\n| pen1 = [[Bert Laing]]\n| try2 = [[Andrew O'Brien (rugby)|Jim O'Brien]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 17\u20138\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title = Knock-Out Competition/Wins For City and Ponsonby\n| page =5\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18832\n| date = 1924-10-06\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19241006.2.31.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]], Ruby, H Hawkes, [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]\n| con1 = [[Nelson Bass]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Hargreaves 2\n| con2 = Mansell\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = McCowatt\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 October\n| time = 1:45\n| home = Athletic\n| score = 21\u20132\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title = Knock-Out Competition\n| page =5\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18832\n| date = 1924-10-06\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19241006.2.31.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Richmond\n| try1 = Hadley, G Yardley, [[Bert Avery]], Webb, [[Ernie Herring]]\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| drop2 = King\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = Saunders\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 October\n| time = 1:45\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 24\u20135\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title = Knock-Out Competition/Wins For City and Ponsonby\n| page =5\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18832\n| date = 1924-10-06\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19241006.2.31.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Mangere\n| try1 = Riley 2, [[Ivan Littlewood]], Shirley, Woodleigh 2\n| con1 = [[Ivan Littlewood]], Shirley\n| pen1 =\n| drop1= [[Eric Grey]]\n| try2 = Marshall\n| con2 = Unknown x 1\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Mincham\n}}\n\n======Semi Finals======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 11 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 29\u201311\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Knock-Out Competition/Interesting Semi-Finals/Wins For City and Ponsonby\n| page =4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18838\n| date = 1924-10-13\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19241013.2.8.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n| away = Athletic\n| try1 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]] 3, Mackie, Sandham, [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] 2\n| con1 = S Crewther, Sandham 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Webb, [[Ernie Herring]], Hadley\n| con2 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 6500\n| referee = W Mincham\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 11 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 14\u201310\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Knock-Out Competition/Interesting Semi-Finals/Wins For City and Ponsonby\n| page =4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18838\n| date = 1924-10-13\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19241013.2.8.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n| away = Devonport\n| try1 = Dempsey, Moore\n| con1 = [[Frank Delgrosso]], Dempsey\n| pen1 = [[Frank Delgrosso]] 2\n| try2 = G Smith, L Voysey\n| con2 = [[Bert Laing]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 2\n| attendance = 6500\n| referee = McCowatt\n}}\n\n======Final======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 18 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 6\u20135\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Defeat Ponsonby/A Strenuous Contest/Score Six Points to Five\n| page =5\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18844\n| date = 1924-10-20\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19241020.2.34.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = Mackie, [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Bill Walsh\n| con2 = [[Frank Delgrosso]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 2000\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n\n==Top Try Scorers and Point Scorers==\nThe lists include points scored in the First Grade competition and the Roope Rooster. Hadley of Devonport United led the league in tries scored with 12, while [[Craddock Dufty]] was once again the top scorer with 91 points from 9 tries, 29 conversions and 3 penalties.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Player!!Team!!Tries\n|-\n|1||J Hadley||Athletic||12\n|-\n|2||[[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]||City Rovers||11\n|-\n|3||A Harper||Devonport United||10\n|-\n|3||Sweeney||Marist Old Boys||10\n|-\n|5||[[Craddock Dufty]]||Athletic||9\n|-\n|5||[[George Gardiner (rugby league)|George Gardiner]]||Marist Old Boys||9\n|-\n|5||M Paul||Mangere United||9\n|-\n|8||[[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]||City Rovers||8\n|-\n|8||Harry Douglas||Devonport United||8\n|-\n|8||L Voysey||Devonport United||8\n|-\n|11||McGregor||Athletic||7\n|-\n|11||[[Andrew O'Brien (rugby)|Jim O'Brien]]||Marist Old Boys||7\n|-\n|11||[[Hec Brisbane]]||Marist Old Boys||7\n|-\n|11||J Stormont||Marist Old Boys||7\n|-\n|11||[[Ivan Littlewood]]||Ponsonby United||7\n|-\n|}\n\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Player!!Team!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Drop Goal!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Craddock Dufty]]||Athletic||9||29||3||0||91\n|-\n|2||[[George Gardiner (rugby league)|George Gardiner]]||Marist Old Boys||9||21||1||0||71\n|-\n|2||[[Frank Delgrosso]]||Ponsonby United||4||15||14||0||70\n|-\n|2||[[Bert Laing]]||Devonport United||6||10||8||0||54\n|-\n|2||A Scott||Devonport United||6||12||0||0||42\n|-\n|2||[[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]||City Rovers||8||7||1||0||40\n|-\n|2||A Mansell||Newton Rangers||4||8||5||0||38\n|-\n|2||S Crewther||City Rovers||4||12||1||0||38\n|-\n|2||J Hadley||Athletic||12||0||0||0||36\n|-\n|2||[[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]||City Rovers||11||1||0||0||35\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\nDevonport had a try and conversion unattributed in a match. While the match between Mangere United and Ellerslie won by Mangere United 18 to 10 had no points attributed to any player. It is possible that M Paul for Mangere scored more tries than the 9 he is credited with and more than the 3 goals he kicked.\n\n== Exhibition Matches and Lower Grades ==\n[[City Rovers]] played Marist of [[Christchurch]] at Carlaw Park in May and were victorious by 16 points to 9. At the end of the season [[Marist Saints|Marist]], who had won the First Grade Championship met [[City Rovers]], who had won the Roope Rooster and the two teams played out a 10 all draw on Monday morning as part of the Labour Day celebrations to officially finish the season for [[Auckland Rugby League]].\n\n======City v Marist (Christchurch)======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 16\u20139\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Not Brilliant But Hard/Interprovincial Club Match/Victory for City/Visitors\u2019 Great Pack\n| page =10\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LV| issue=123\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240526.2.157\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n \n| away = Marist (Christchurch)\n| try1 = S Crewther, G Reid 2, Sutton\n| con1 = S Crewther 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Batchelor\n| con2 = C Fitzgerald\n| pen2 = C Fitzgerald, Brosnahan\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 10000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n\n======City v Marist======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 10\u201310\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Marist and City Draw/After a Great Game\n| page =3\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LV| issue=255\n| date = 1924-10-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19241027.2.21\n| accessdate = 2020-03-31}}</ref>\n \n| away = Marist\n| try1 = [[Nelson Bass]], [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]\n| con1 = S Crewther\n| pen1 = E Brown\n| try2 = Malloy, [[Jack Kirwan (rugby league)|Jack Kirwan]]\n| con2 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]]\n| pen2 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]]\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 4000\n| referee =\n}}\n\n== Lower Grades ==\nThere were 6 lower grades in 1924 if you include the Sixth Grade which was split into an A and B grade. Grades were made of the following teams with the winning team in bold:\n*'''Second Grade''': Athletics, City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Kingsland, Manukau, Marist, Newton, '''Otahuhu''', Ponsonby, Richmond, United Suburbs\n*'''Third Grade''': Athletics, City, Coromandel Old Boys, Devonport, Kingsland, Mangere, Manukau, New Lynn, Otahuhu, Parnell, Ponsonby, Richmond, Suburbs\n*'''Fourth Grade''': City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Mangere, Manukau, Marist, Newton, Parnell, Ponsonby A, Ponsonby B, Richmond, United Suburbs, Takapuna\n*'''Fifth Grade''': Athletics, Ellerslie, Manukau, New Lynn, Newton, Northcote, Otahuhu, Ponsonby, Point Chevalier, Richmond\n*'''Sixth Grade A''': '''Athletics A''', Athletics B, City A, City B, Devonport, Ellerslie, Ley Institute, Manukau, Marist Brothers A, Marist Brothers B, Newton, Parnell, Ponsonby, Richmond\n*'''Sixth Grade B''': Athletics, City, Ellerslie, Manukau, Parnell, Richmond\n\n== Representative Fixtures ==\n[[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] played three matches against [[Australian Universities Rugby League|Australian Universities]] on 4, 7, and 14 June. In the first match [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] defeated the University side by 15 to 7. In the second meeting [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] again won, this time more easily by 17 points to 2. The visiting captain congratulated the [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] team but made mention of the conditions by saying that \u201cyours are certainly better wet day footballers than we are but this is to be expected when you realise that my club, [[Sydney University]] has not played on a wet ground since early in 1922 season\u201d.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Comments By Visitors/Captain and Manager/Hope for Dry Ground\n| page =4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18730\n| date = 1923-06-09\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240609.2.16.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref> They had their wish somewhat in the third match with much improved weather conditions and were able to come home strongly in the second half to draw the match 14\u201314 in front of 11,500 people.\n\nOn 26 July in front of 20,000 spectators the touring [[England national rugby league team|England]] side defeated [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] by 24 points to 11. In the curtain-raisers [[Ellerslie Eagles|Ellerslie]] Sixth Grade B defeated [[City Rovers|City]] Sixth Grade B by 5 points to 2, and [[City Rovers|City]] Second grade defeated their [[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond]] counterparts by 8 points to 7. On the Wednesday following, an Auckland provincial team featuring Auckland players from the greater region including the [[Waikato]] region played [[England rugby league team|England]] and lost 28 to 13 in front of 7,000 spectators.\n\nOn 20 September an Auckland team played [[Waikato rugby league team|South Auckland]] in [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]] and were defeated easily by 21 points to 5. The team was supposed to be a full strength [[Auckland Rugby League|Auckland]] team but as the club competition was entering its key stages many of the first team players remained behind to play for their clubs. As a result many players from the struggling [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] team made the trip to [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]].<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Win for South Auckland/Auckland Defeated By 21 To 5/Mediocre Representative Team\n| page =4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18820\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240922.2.7.5\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n\n===Auckland v Australian Universities===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 15\u20137\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Visiting League Team/Australian Universities/Auckland Wins First Game/Fifteen Points to Seven/Superiority Throughout\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18727\n| date = 1924-06-05\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240605.2.124\n| accessdate = 2019-09-05}}</ref>\n| away = Australian Universities\n| try1 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]], [[Ivan Littlewood]] 2\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[Bert Laing]]\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| try2 = Barry\n| con2 = Ryan\n| pen2 = Ryan\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = Neild\n}}\n\n===Auckland v Australian Universities===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 17\u20132\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Beaten Again/Aussies\u2019 Poor Exhibition/Auckland Too Good/Football in the Mud\n| page =10\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LV| issue=135\n| date = 1924-06-09\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240609.2.122\n| accessdate = 2019-09-05}}</ref>\n| away = Australian Universities\n| try1 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]], McNeil, [[Nelson Bass]]\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 3\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Ryan\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 4000\n| referee = A Gallagher\n}}\n\n===Auckland v Australian Universities===\n[[Frank Delgrosso]] had to come on the replace [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]] after he collided badly with team mate [[Clarrie Polson]] when they were both going after the ball. Polson received a bad cut over his eye and he also later had to retire and was replaced by Billy Ghent.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 14 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 14\u20134\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Universities and Auckland Draw/Thrilling Second Half/Visitors Dashing Backs\n| page =9\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LV| issue=141\n| date = 1924-06-16\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240616.2.122\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n| away = Australian Universities\n| try1 = [[Bert Laing]] 2, [[Clarrie Polson]], Harry Douglas\n| con1 = [[Maurice Wetherill]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Ryan 2, O\u2019Rourke, Halberstater\n| con2 = Dunworth\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 12000\n| referee = W Ripley\n}}\n\n===Probables v Possibles Trial Match===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 14 June\n| time = 1:30\n| home = Probables\n| score = 9\u201314\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Possibles v Probables/Win for Possibles\n| page =9\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LV| issue=141\n| date = 1924-06-16\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240616.2.125\n| accessdate = 2020-03-31}}</ref>\n| away = Possibles\n| try1 = Paul, Webb, Veart\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Hec Brisbane]], Peebles 2, [[Ernie Herring]]\n| con2 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 12000\n| referee = W. L. Bull\n}}\n\n===Auckland B v Hamilton===\n[[Wilson Hall (rugby league)|Wilson Hall]] broke his collar bone during the second half and had to leave the field.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 16 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland B\n| score = 28\u201318\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Hamilton Team Beaten/Success of Local Players/An Interesting Contest\n| page =6\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18763\n| date = 1924-07-28\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240717.2.11.1\n| accessdate = 2020-03-31}}</ref>\n| away = Hamilton\n| try1 = [[Bill Te Whata]] 2, Shirley 2, Paul, [[Ivan Littlewood]]\n| con1 = [[Wilson Hall (rugby league)|Wilson Hall]], [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]] 2\n| pen1 = Shirley, Mason\n| try2 = McGerty, Hemingway\n| con2 = Dufty 2\n| pen2 = Dufty 3\n| drop2 =Hemingway\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Mincham\n}}\n\n===Auckland v England===\nIn scoring on halftime [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]] was knocked out. At the start of the second half Auckland attempted to replace him with [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] who ran out on to the field. However the England captain when seeing this objected as replacements were forbidden in the second half of rugby league matches at this time. Auckland were forced to play with 12 players for a time until Davidson recovered well enough to return to the field.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 26 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 11\u201324\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Match Against Auckland/Win for the Visitors/Twenty-Four to Eleven/Excellent Combined Play\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18772\n| date = 1924-07-28\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240728.2.129\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n| away = England\n| try1 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]] 2, [[Nelson Bass]]\n| con1 =\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| try2 = Ring 2, Evans, Bennett, Carr, Whitty\n| con2 = Parkin, Knapman\n| pen2 = Parkin\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 20000\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n\n===Auckland Province v England===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 30 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland Province\n| score = 13\u201328\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =English League Team/Match Against Province/Twenty-Eight to Thirteen/Good Local Forwards/Visitors\u2019 Backs Superior\n| page =11\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18775\n| date = 1924-07-31\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240731.2.132\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = England\n| try1 = [[Hec Brisbane]], B Johnston, [[Frank Delgrosso]]\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| try2 = Gronow, Rix, Howley 2, Darwell, Price\n| con2 = Gronow 4\n| pen2 = Gronow\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = Field\n}}\n\n===Auckland B v Lower Waikato===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland B\n| score = 15\u201314\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Lower Waikato Match/Auckland\u2019s Narrow Victory/Fifteen Points to Fourteen\n| page = 6\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXI| issue=18793\n| date = 1924-08-21\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240821.2.10.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref>\n| away = Lower Waikato\n| try1 = Shirley, H Hawkes, McDonald\n| con1 = Mansell 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Hall, W Jackson, Welch, Alman\n| con2 = Hall\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Bovaird\n}}\n\n===Auckland v South Auckland (Waikato)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = South Auckland (Waikato)\n| score = 21\u20135\n| report = <