ice]]\n| [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem Region]]\n| {{Success|Home isolation}}\n| Female\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | Women (case No. 29, #30) from a group that visited Auronzo di Cadore ski resort in Italy.<ref name=\"cases29-30-twitter\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''31'''\n| 8 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}}\n| {{Partial failure|Person-to-person spread}}\n| {{flagicon|CZE}} family\n| {{n/a}}\n| [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem Region]]\n| {{Success|Home isolation}}\n| Male\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | An elderly man, a relative of cases No. 29 and No. 30, who had not visited Italy.<ref name=case31-twitter>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/adamvojtechano/status/1236675420826861568|title=Twitter update from Minister of Health|via=Twitter|access-date=8 March 2020}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''32'''\n| 8 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}}\n| {{Partial failure|Person-to-person spread}}\n| {{flagicon|CZE}} known connection\n| [[Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9]]\n| [[Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9 Region]]\n| {{Success|Home isolation}}\n| Male\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | A man tested at University Hospital Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9 was in contact with a Prague coronavirus case\u2014a person who had been infected in Boston (case No. 15 or #22).<ref name=\"case27-32.idnes\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''33'''\n| 9 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}} \n| {{Success|Travel-related}}\n| {{flag|Italy}}, [[Trentino]]\n| [[Ro\u017enov pod Radho\u0161t\u011bm]]\n| [[Zl\u00edn Region]]\n| {{n/a}}\n| Female\n| ~42\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | A woman (*1978) who had been on a family holiday in Trentino, Italy. She had mild respiratory issues.<ref name=\"